This crate (gto-today-solver-wasm) is licensed under AGPL-3.0 because
it links to postflop-solver, which is AGPL-3.0. Any derivative work
— including modifications and re-bundlings — must itself be AGPL-3.0
and make source available to any user who interacts with the software
over a network.

The gto.today application (https://gto.today) consumes this package
via npm dependency and HTTP-only runtime calls; under AGPL-3.0
"mere aggregation" this does not force the main app's source to be
published. This distinction is preserved only by keeping this
package separate and unmodified.
